Ratio&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;isOverlayTextVisible&amp;quot;&amp;#58;true,&amp;quot;isCaptionEnabled&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;minimumLayoutWidth&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;customContentDropSupport&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;externallink&amp;quot;&amp;#125;,&amp;quot;containsDynamicDataSource&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false&amp;#125;&quot;&gt;&lt;div data-sp-componentid=&quot;d1d91016-032f-456d-98a4-721247c305e8&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div data-sp-htmlproperties=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img data-sp-prop-name=&quot;imageSource&quot; src=&quot;/sites/GlobalHR/SiteAssets/SitePages/Digital/2479029434-38cc9390978929231b424ad15a7c1dc022175581.png&quot; data-sp-cust-siteid=&quot;be586e5c-f14e-465a-a7f0-5bf5a8049e74&quot; data-sp-cust-webid=&quot;5822877b-80cb-40b2-8e63-22ef750ca0ea&quot; data-sp-cust-listid=&quot;1569357f-d947-4e53-b160-67fe3ec4e250&quot; data-sp-cust-uniqueid=&quot;86496dbc-f047-463c-b26f-128b9e6d1480&quot; data-sp-cust-width=&quot;1057&quot; data-sp-cust-height=&quot;441&quot; /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div data-sp-canvascontrol=&quot;&quot; data-sp-canvasdataversion=&quot;1.0&quot; data-sp-controldata=&quot;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;position&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;layoutIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;zoneIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;8,&amp;quot;zoneId&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;a5e94be3-0259-4f5d-9522-56ddaa80d298&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;sectionIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;sectionFactor&amp;quot;&amp;#58;12,&amp;quot;controlIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1&amp;#125;,&amp;quot;emphasis&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;zoneEmphasis&amp;quot;&amp;#58;2&amp;#125;,&amp;quot;id&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;e1661873-c6d6-4fae-a96a-60d0db2dde0c&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;controlType&amp;quot;&amp;#58;4,&amp;quot;isFromSectionTemplate&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;addedFromPersistedData&amp;quot;&amp;#58;true,&amp;quot;contentVersion&amp;quot;&amp;#58;5&amp;#125;&quot;&gt;&lt;div data-sp-rte=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apply&amp;#58;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Applications will open based on the business demand where eligible GenC associates can apply for the roles by submitting the survey within the stipulated timeline.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualify&amp;#58;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;To qualify for the program, GenC associates have to fulfill a specific criterion by taking an assessment / interview for pre-requisite skills. It may vary for each role and MDU/SL. Qualifying criteria for each role will be specified in the page, linked to the list of roles mentioned in the table above.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Certify&amp;#58;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Post qualification, sign up to learn and get certified in the required skills for the GenC Next / GenC Pro roles. The associates&#39; current work deliverables should not be affected during this learning phase. Depending on the niche nature of the roles, the participants may need to go through multiple stages of learning and certification to get selected and deployed into the GenC Next / GenC Pro roles. It may be a&amp;#160;MDU/SL&amp;#160;defined assessment or MDU/SL recognized certifications. Details for each role will be specified in the page, linked to the list of roles mentioned in the table above.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Selection&amp;#58;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Post certification, the GenC associates would be interviewed by the project teams and who clears the evaluation will be shortlisted for the next phase&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deployment&amp;#58;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul class=&quot;customListStyle&quot;&gt;&lt;li data-list-item-id=&quot;e98b08e298de97a8f60464339ee2b976c&quot;&gt;The movement to GenC Next / GenC Pro role (allocation to upskilled role) is mandatory for GenCs to receive the Honors benefit.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-list-item-id=&quot;e8fe5815dd364e37b877fa5355c3f551e&quot;&gt;The movement will be initiated only after identifying a billable position in the target SL. Till then, the GenC associates are required to continue in their home SL.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-list-item-id=&quot;ec381bd46c0bbf4dbbcd9e57dbad30349&quot;&gt;There would be 4-6 weeks of prior notice provided to the GenC associate’s 3 level supervisors, wherever Department Transfer and/or Project change is required&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grade wise Honors benefit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul class=&quot;customListStyle&quot; style=&quot;list-style-type&amp;#58;disc;&quot;&gt;&lt;li data-list-item-id=&quot;ef71e46bb16a12a0055aecc747b46efe7&quot;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;strong&gt;If the applicant is a PA at the time of enrollment and completes the Honors program as a PA or A&lt;/strong&gt;, then the GenC Next Comp benefit will happen in the subsequent month after movement into the project on the skills acquired through Honors&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-list-item-id=&quot;eb2a3fd4403528463796ab2bff7e58440&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;noSpacingAbove noSpacingBelow&quot; data-text-type=&quot;noSpacing&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If the applicant is a PAT at the time of enrollment and completes the Honors program as a PAT&lt;/strong&gt;, then GenC Next Comp benefit will happen in the subsequent month after PA confirmation. The movement to the GenC Next role depends on the release approval from the current project team on or before 18 months from DOJ&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-list-item-id=&quot;e1d8f5edabf8d2c419caca7f77740a081&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;noSpacingAbove noSpacingBelow&quot; data-text-type=&quot;noSpacing&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If the applicant is a PAT at the time of enrollment and completes the Honors program as a PA&lt;/strong&gt;, then GenC Next Comp benefit will happen in the subsequent month from the time of Honors completion. The movement to the GenC Next role depends on the release approval from the current project team on or before 18 months from DOJ&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;noSpacingAbove noSpacingBelow&quot; data-text-type=&quot;noSpacing&quot;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Note&amp;#58;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#160;Applicants who clear the Certify and Selection phase of the program, the project movement will be initiated only after identifying a billable position. Till then, the applicants are required to continue in their home project where we’ll give 4-6 weeks of prior notice to your supervisor for the project movement.&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;There is change in the guidelines for &#39;Grade wise honors benefit&#39; for the roles launched from Mar 2023 onwards. Please find the new guidelines in the role specific page&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div data-sp-canvascontrol=&quot;&quot; data-sp-canvasdataversion=&quot;1.0&quot; data-sp-controldata=&quot;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;position&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;layoutIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;zoneIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;9,&amp;quot;zoneId&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;ca588e11-a7a7-4e55-8b59-86d05aebfc4b&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;sectionIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;sectionFactor&amp;quot;&amp;#58;4,&amp;quot;controlIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1&amp;#125;,&amp;quot;id&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;d5853542-0aef-4174-ab6b-0038c4d04a9f&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;controlType&amp;quot;&amp;#58;3,&amp;quot;isFromSectionTemplate&amp;quot;&amp;#58;true,&amp;quot;addedFromPersistedData&amp;quot;&amp;#58;true,&amp;quot;webPartId&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;d1d91016-032f-456d-98a4-721247c305e8&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;reservedWidth&amp;quot;&amp;#58;352,&amp;quot;reservedHeight&amp;quot;&amp;#58;370&amp;#125;&quot;&gt;&lt;div data-sp-webpart=&quot;&quot; data-sp-webpartdataversion=&quot;1.11&quot; data-sp-webpartdata=&quot;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;id&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;d1d91016-032f-456d-98a4-721247c305e8&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;instance