uot; data-sp-cust-uniqueid=&quot;ecaf8d90-7531-478e-8b88-c462112fe921&quot; data-sp-cust-width=&quot;2918&quot; data-sp-cust-height=&quot;418&quot; /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div data-sp-canvascontrol=&quot;&quot; data-sp-canvasdataversion=&quot;1.0&quot; data-sp-controldata=&quot;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;position&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;layoutIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;zoneIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;12,&amp;quot;zoneId&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;15a42f0d-5238-472c-92b0-faf53846a2b0&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;sectionIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;sectionFactor&amp;quot;&amp;#58;12,&amp;quot;controlIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1&amp;#125;,&amp;quot;emphasis&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;zoneEmphasis&amp;quot;&amp;#58;2&amp;#125;,&amp;quot;id&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;5f716f9d-1f85-424d-9da2-de0eee0d814f&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;controlType&amp;quot;&amp;#58;4,&amp;quot;isFromSectionTemplate&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;addedFromPersistedData&amp;quot;&amp;#58;true,&amp;quot;contentVersion&amp;quot;&amp;#58;5&amp;#125;&quot;&gt;&lt;div data-sp-rte=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ASSOCIATE FAQS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div data-sp-canvascontrol=&quot;&quot; data-sp-canvasdataversion=&quot;1.0&quot; data-sp-controldata=&quot;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;position&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;layoutIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;zoneIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;13,&amp;quot;zoneId&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;61d19e10-bb84-4244-a67e-8c687965686c&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;sectionIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;sectionFactor&amp;quot;&amp;#58;12,&amp;quot;controlIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1&amp;#125;,&amp;quot;zoneGroupMetadata&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;type&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;isExpanded&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;showDividerLine&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;iconAlignment&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;left&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;displayName&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;Apply Phase&amp;quot;&amp;#125;,&amp;quot;id&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;c74d25f4-cbdf-406a-8b94-45a8c7a93123&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;controlType&amp;quot;&amp;#58;4,&amp;quot;isFromSectionTemplate&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;addedFromPersistedData&amp;quot;&amp;#58;true,&amp;quot;contentVersion&amp;quot;&amp;#58;5&amp;#125;&quot;&gt;&lt;div data-sp-rte=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I am not from the Service Line where the role is launched. Can I still apply being in a different Service Line?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It differs for each role, based on BU demand. So, you may please check the role specific page to check the eligibility.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How do we know our application status after submitting the survey?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Applicants are required to wait till the survey window is closed. The Digital Honors team will evaluate the applications to check the eligibility before they send the application status. This would take additional of 2-3 working days.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I am already pursuing a role through Digital Honors. So, can I apply for the newly launched role/s?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Applicant can actively participate only in one role at a time. The application will be rejected if he/she apply for new role while actively participating in Certify phase of any other role.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I am expecting a specific role launch or a new batch of an existing role, when can we expect?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Digital Honors program is launched to supply GenC Next / GenC Pro positions based on BU demand. Hence, new positions will be opened as and when we receive new demand. Appropriate communication would be sent to the target audience.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I am a PAT participating in Honors program, will I be moved to a higher order role in the same project or a different project, after successful completion?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;First you get confirmed as a PA (GenC Next) at the end of 12&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;#160;month after successful completion of Honors. Post that, the project team will have max 6 months of time for higher order role rotation within the same project or a different project.&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I&amp;#160;am a PAT, joined recently after my internship; will the 6 months be considered along with internship period?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;No, 6 months will be considered from the day of joining as a Full Time Employee (FTE).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I am less tenured than 6 months, am I eligible to enroll for this program?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It is mandatory for an applicant to complete minimum 6 months with Cognizant as per the cutoff date specified in the announcement / table above. However, you can apply in the subsequent cycle once you are eligible.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I am already a GenC Next, can I still apply for Honors program?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The program is for GenCs to get elevated to GenC Pro/Next role, so you will not be eligible for the program.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Can I apply anytime to this program?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The timeline for submitting your application will be open for one week from the day of job posting, and the program will run for 3-4 months. The survey link would not be active after specified time and you are required to wait for the next cycle.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What if I fail in ‘Qualifying’ criteria but am still interested in this job/role?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Do not worry, the program will be open as and when we receive demand from BU. So, get yourself prepared and apply in next cycle.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How many roles can I apply for?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You can apply only for one role at a time and you should choose an appropriate role where your current capabilities match with the pre-requisites.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Should I get approval from my supervisor for applying this program?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Yes, it is mandatory to inform your supervisor before applying for this program.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What if my current supervisor is not releasing me from the project after successful completion?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;There will be enough time for your supervisor to plan, as the whole process will take 3 - 4 months for a PA level &amp;amp; additional 6 months for PAT level from the time they become PA. The supervisor should share a tentative date for the approval, with the associate. For further support on this, you may reach out to your HR Business Partner.&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I am currently billable in a project; would I be released after completing this program successfully?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Yes, you will be moved into a GenC Next / GenC Pro role within the same project or to a different project, based on the role you apply for, and MDU/SL requirement.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I am a tenured associate at PA level and expecting a promotion in the coming cycle. Can I still go ahead and apply?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;GenCs at PA level who are due for promotion can still participate in this program to take up the GenC Next / GenC Pro role.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I am from Digital Business Operations. Am I eligible for this program?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is exclusively for PATs and PAs in IT Services as mentioned in the eligibility criteria. So, it would not be applicable for DBO associates.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I am eligible for the program as per the eligibility criteria, but I was not considered for the program stating that I am from a different Service Line. Can you please clarify?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Few roles are specific to the role launched Service Line where they restrict the other Service Line applicants to apply considering the demand. You may also go through that role/batch specific page for more details.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div data-sp-canvascontrol=&quot;&quot; data-sp-canvasdataversion=&quot;1.0&quot; data-sp-controldata=&quot;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;position&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;layoutIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;zoneIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;14,&amp;quot;zoneId&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;ff7d9144-1b1c-4ee7-9c26-2872b10c3f2f&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;sectionIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;sectionFactor&amp;quot;&amp;#58;12,&amp;quot;controlIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1&amp;#125;,&amp;quot;zoneGroupMetadata&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;type&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;isExpanded&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;showDividerLine&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;iconAlignment&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;left&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;displayName&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;Certify Phase&amp;quot;&amp;#125;,&amp;quot;id&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;63734282-899e-446b-9f98-8cc4dad26953&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;controlType&amp;quot;&amp;#58;4,&amp;quot;isFromSectionTemplate&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;addedFromPersistedData&amp;quot;&amp;#58;true,&amp;quot;contentVersion&amp;quot;&amp;#58;5&amp;#125;&quot;&gt;&lt;div data-sp-rte=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do we get any certification for completing the Honors program?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;No certification is issued for Honors completion.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Will the resources and study material, provided by Cognizant?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It is completely self-paced learning and practice; however, we will provide guidance and information about learning resources. You can leverage additional learning resources like ‘Cognizant Learn,’ and ‘Udemy’ platforms to upskill yourselves.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Will I get dedicated time-off from the current project deliverables to participate in this program?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;No, there should not be any impact to the current project deliverables, and you are required to participate in this program during your non-project hours.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are the assessments in Certify phase proctored?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Yes, the assessment platform is enabled with Plagiarism checks and enabled with remote proctoring. Hence, anyone found to have plagiarism as per the platform report, will be disqualified from the program.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If I do not certify on the required skills / do not clear the interview, will I get a chance again to re-attempt?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If the participant does not clear the learning and certification, the opportunity for final selection will be lost for this cycle, however, you can participate/apply again in the next cycle.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What if I am already certified with the mentioned criteria? Am I still eligible for this program?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you are already certified with the mentioned criteria, you could still apply for the program as per the timeline. However, you can skip the Qualify and Certify phase and directly participate in the Selection phase, aligned to this program timeline.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What if I need to go through a project change while participating in this program?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Associate must upfront inform the new supervisor about his application &amp;amp; participation in this program and have their alignment.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is cooling off period mentioned in few role specific workflows?&amp;#160;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Cooling off period is the period one gets allocated to a project in the Service Line mentioned and get the real project hands-on experience.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div data-sp-canvascontrol=&quot;&quot; data-sp-canvasdataversion=&quot;1.0&quot; data-sp-controldata=&quot;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;position&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;layoutIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;zoneIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;15,&amp;quot;zoneId&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;fcd179d6-68c6-4bb7-8eb6-dac8f8ba5f9e&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;sectionIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;sectionFactor&amp;quot;&amp;#58;12,&amp;quot;controlIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1&amp;#125;,&amp;quot;zoneGroupMetadata&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;type&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;isExpanded&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;showDividerLine&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;iconAlignment&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;left&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;displayName&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;Qualify Phase&amp;quot;&amp;#125;,&amp;quot;id&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;c273e9da-2393-4726-989e-96eb8af57ea6&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;controlType&amp;quot;&amp;#58;4,&amp;quot;isFromSectionTemplate&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;addedFromPersistedData&amp;quot;&amp;#58;true,&amp;quot;contentVersion&amp;quot;&amp;#58;5&amp;#125;&quot;&gt;&lt;div data-sp-rte=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;​​​​​​​&lt;strong&gt;Can I know the assessment score/s that I have secured in qualifier assessment?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The individual scores cannot be shared. Please be informed that the assessments are administered in the industry standard platform and the results are also validated for accuracy by GenC Solution SMEs. &amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What would be the pattern of assessment?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Assessments could be a combination of Skill Based &amp;amp; Knowledge based. It may be either one of these, as per the role requirement. So, it is advised to be prepared and clear the assessment, irrespective of the&amp;#160;pattern.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I couldn’t attend the qualifier assessment due to power cut / Internet issue /&amp;#160;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;technical glitch etc., will I be provided with another attempt?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We recommend the applicants to have proper power / internet backup and do system-check before starting the assessment. We are giving prior information and enough time to plan well for the assessment, considering weekdays and weekend combination. So, no additional attempts will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Can I apply for the same role in next instance/future if I am unable to qualify in the current batch?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Yes, if the applicant fails to clear the Qualify/Certify in the curret cycle, they can apply in next instance/next cycle/new role.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How will I know whether my application&amp;#160;is considered for the program?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You will receive an email after validation, for both scenarios – whether you are considered to move forward, or your application is not eligible to proceed.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where can I see the details about the qualifying process?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Qualifier may vary for each service line. You can view the link provided against each role in the table above for role specific details.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Should I be aware of the skill before applying a role?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Each role has different pre-requisites, so please go through the details about the role thoroughly before applying. You can check the link provided against each role in the table above for role specific details.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How may rounds of interview do I need to go through?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;During the Qualify phase, there will be only one round of the interview for the applied role. However, further rounds of interviews might be required based on MDU/SL requirement&amp;#160;at the time of final selection.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div data-sp-canvascontrol=&quot;&quot; data-sp-canvasdataversion=&quot;1.0&quot; data-sp-controldata=&quot;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;position&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;layoutIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;zoneIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;16,&amp;quot;zoneId&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;485025a8-6134-49bd-bfac-5ba12816a86e&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;sectionIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;sectionFactor&amp;quot;&amp;#58;12,&amp;quot;controlIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1&amp;#125;,&amp;quot;zoneGroupMetadata&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;type&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;isExpanded&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;showDividerLine&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;iconAlignment&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;left&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;displayName&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;Selection Phase&amp;quot;&amp;#125;,&amp;quot;id&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;e2212ebf-eea2-4a2c-bffb-7a328c4949c1&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;controlType&amp;quot;&amp;#58;4,&amp;quot;isFromSectionTemplate&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;addedFromPersistedData&amp;quot;&amp;#58;true,&amp;quot;contentVersion&amp;quot;&amp;#58;5&amp;#125;&quot;&gt;&lt;div data-sp-rte=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I am pursuing Honors role for the skill which is not launched from my Service Line. Is Department transfer mandatory?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It depends on the role you are currently pursuing, below are the options&amp;#58;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Department transfer is mandatory where the role demands the applicant’s movement to target service line and complete the final exit criteria to get the Honors benefit&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Few roles can hold the applicant in same service line when the current BU can fulfil the GenC Next positions if the skill matches with Honors completed skill&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;When should I get Department transfer? How long will that take?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Department transfer process will be initiated post the successful completion of Certify phase i.e., during the 2 - 4 weeks of Selection &amp;amp; Deploy phase and depends on the availability of billable position in the target service line. The usual timeline is 2-4 weeks; however, you may experience a delay if there are any project dependencies /deliverables etc. which may take additional weeks.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As an applicant, what is my role in Department Transfer?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It is important for you to inform/discuss with your HCM supervisor and EDL/PDL about your participation in Honors program and update him/her at every stage along with the timeline of completion.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What if I don’t get a billable role post completion?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Open positions are published based on the critical business requirements and it is very unlikely the selected candidates will not end up into the target role.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Will I be interviewed even after I clear the certify phase?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Post your skilling and certification process, the certified applicants will be interviewed for GenC Next / GenC Pro roles.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div data-sp-canvascontrol=&quot;&quot; data-sp-canvasdataversion=&quot;1.0&quot; data-sp-controldata=&quot;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;position&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;layoutIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;zoneIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;17,&amp;quot;zoneId&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;d2bde6d2-155a-4e99-a8b1-e13a70fb45b9&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;sectionIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;sectionFactor&amp;quot;&amp;#58;12,&amp;quot;controlIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1&amp;#125;,&amp;quot;zoneGroupMetadata&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;type&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;isExpanded&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;showDividerLine&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;iconAlignment&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;left&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;displayName&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;Deployment Phase&amp;quot;&amp;#125;,&amp;quot;id&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;3f3a0967-5a83-4ab1-ba97-3ade106f6c18&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;controlType&amp;quot;&amp;#58;4,&amp;quot;isFromSectionTemplate&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;addedFromPersistedData&amp;quot;&amp;#58;true,&amp;quot;contentVersion&amp;quot;&amp;#58;5&amp;#125;&quot;&gt;&lt;div data-sp-rte=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I have joined Honors program as PAT, but I have become a PA during the Certify phase. Will I follow PA workflow or PAT workflow as mentioned in role specific page?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The grade at the time of application process will be considered, hence you will have to follow PAT workflow.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If I move to GenC Next / GenC Pro role through this program, is there any bond that I sign with Cognizant?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Absolutely No, Cognizant believes in a no-bond culture.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If I move to GenC Next / GenC Pro role, will I be positioned in the same location that I am working currently?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Your location of work will be dependent on the open positions available/applied for the GenC Next / GenC Pro roles as per business requirements.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I am in certify phase of Honors program and will complete in the next 1 or 2 months. Currently, I am in bench/PDP/CDP/VCDP. So, can I wait for department transfer to take up the role in the target SL?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Honors movement will happen only after identifying the billable position in the target Service Line/Project. So, we recommend the applicant to take up the assignment in the current project.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is an SO?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;SO is a Service Order where an ID will be created again your name for the GenC Next role upon completing the Honors program.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who creates / validates an SO and what is the cutoff date?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;SO can be created by a project manager or a Proxy project manager from the project where the applicant would be moving. It will be then validated and approved by the applicant’s Operations Excellence (OE). If it gets created on or before 12&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;#160;of any month, then the comp hike would be processed in that month.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;When will be the compensation hike processed after creating and approving the SO?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The comp hike would be processed in the same month (as per the cutoff date mentioned above) where an applicant will receive the eLetter in the last week of that month with 1&lt;sup&gt;st&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;#160;as effective date.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Am I eligible for the comp hike if I am in notice period or applied resignation?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;No, an applicant would not be eligible for comp hike if he/she applied for resignation or serving notice period.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I an applicant is in PIP (Performance Improvement Plan), will participation in Honors help them to get into a GenC Next project?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If an applicant applies for the same SL role, then GenC Next SO would not be created by the project if an applicant is in PIP and Honors team would not proceed with the next steps of processing comp hike.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If an applicant applies for the other SL role, the movement would not be approved by the target SL if an applicant is in PIP and Honors team would not proceed with the next steps of processing comp hike.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What would be the enhanced compensation if I move to GenC Next role / GenC Pro role through this program?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Currently, the compensation is 6.75&amp;#160;ATR (Annual Total Remuneration)&amp;#160;for GenC Next role and 5.40&amp;#160;ATR (Annual Total Remuneration)&amp;#160;for GenC Pro role.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How will the promotion cycle from PA to A change if I participate in this program?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;GenC Next PA to A level Promotion will follow the regular PA to A process.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Will my performance evaluation be impacted if I move to a new project?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The performance appraisal process for associates moving to new roles will remain the same. At the time of roll-off, the associate should initiate a project-end review with their home manager and request documented, detailed feedback. The new home manager should review the feedback and complete a comprehensive year-end appraisal to represent the associate in the calibration process. An associate’s appraisal rating shall not be impacted due to a job move.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Whom can I contact for more questions/information?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;For questions, please contact&amp;#160;&lt;a data-cke-saved-href=&quot;mailto&amp;#58;GenCDigitalHonors@Cognizant.com&quot; href=&quot;mailto&amp;#58;GenCDigitalHonors@Cognizant.com&quot;&gt;GenCDigitalHonors@Cognizant.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div data-sp-canvascontrol=&quot;&quot; data-sp-canvasdataversion=&quot;1.0&quot; data-sp-controldata=&quot;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;position&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;layoutIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;zoneIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;18,&amp;quot;zoneId&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;cccffbda-7cd2-495f-a51b-02d9c5971274&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;sectionIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;sectionFactor&amp;quot;&amp;#58;12,&amp;quot;controlIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1&amp;#125;,&amp;quot;emphasis&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;zoneEmphasis&amp;quot;&amp;#58;2&amp;#125;,&amp;quot;id&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;2f3bd057-f003-445a-a3ae-44aa33473815&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;controlType&amp;quot;&amp;#58;4,&amp;quot;isFromSectionTemplate&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;addedFromPersistedData&amp;quot;&amp;#58;true,&amp;quot;contentVersion&amp;quot;&amp;#58;5&amp;#125;&quot;&gt;&lt;div data-sp-rte=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SUPERVISOR FAQS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div data-sp-canvascontrol=&quot;&quot; data-sp-canvasdataversion=&quot;1.0&quot; data-sp-controldata=&quot;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;position&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;layoutIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;zoneIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;19,&amp;quot;zoneId&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;1318370e-7ff4-4b1d-9f6e-d57d003eb3b5&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;sectionIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;sectionFactor&amp;quot;&amp;#58;12,&amp;quot;controlIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1&amp;#125;,&amp;quot;zoneGroupMetadata&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;type&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;isExpanded&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;showDividerLine&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;iconAlignment&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;left&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;displayName&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;Set 1&amp;quot;&amp;#125;,&amp;quot;id&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;2261dbd1-7f52-4094-aca8-ea9f3111bdde&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;controlType&amp;quot;&amp;#58;4,&amp;quot;isFromSectionTemplate&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;addedFromPersistedData&amp;quot;&amp;#58;true,&amp;quot;contentVersion&amp;quot;&amp;#58;5&amp;#125;&quot;&gt;&lt;div data-sp-rte=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We would like to retain the Honors applicant by providing GenC Next / GenC Pro role as my current project has the same skill. What should we do?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Current project team can retain the applicant by providing the GenC Next / GenC Pro SO for the same Honors role if there are open positions. However, there are few roles which demands the completion of Honors in 2 steps where applicant should move to target SL and complete the final exit criteria. In such cases, applicant cannot be retained in the same project.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is a GenC Next / GenC Pro role SO and what guidelines should we follow to create?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;GenC Next / GenC Pro SO guidelines&amp;#58;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;•&amp;#160; GenC Next / GenC Pro SO can be created similar to any PA SO&amp;#160;&lt;br&gt;•&amp;#160; Primary Skill – Certified skill through Honors program&lt;br&gt;•&amp;#160; Secondary skill – Certified skill through Honors program&lt;br&gt;•&amp;#160; Any notes/comments section – Movement as part of Digital Honors program&lt;br&gt;•&amp;#160; Critical flag marking of SO&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is the role of a supervisor in the GenC Digital Honors program?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A supervisor should&amp;#58;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;a. Be aware and clear about the intent of this program&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;b. Encourage and empower eligible associates to be able to actively participate in this program&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;c. Plan for the rotation of the participating GenCs’ after successful completion of the program&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Can a supervisor deny the associate’s request to participate in GenC Digital Honors?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The objective of the program is to empower eligible associates to meet their development goals and career aspirations. However, in certain instances like an associate is a named resource in the client Master Service Agreement (MSA) – the request may be deferred for the next cycle. The supervisor should educate the associate about this program and its recurrence and ask them to apply in the subsequent cycle.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How will I know if my team member has applied for a role or has been shortlisted/rejected?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The associate who applies will be notified along with a copy to the supervisor, once they are&amp;#58;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Shortlisted during application phase&amp;#160;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Qualify for the Certify phase&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How long we should retain the associates and plan for the rotation after they enroll for the program?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Once the associates get shortlisted for the Certify phase, it will take approximately 3-4 months to move to deploy phase for a PA level associates. And for&amp;#160;PATs, an additional 6 months from the time they become PA.&amp;#160;So, you may please plan accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Is there a system approval required from supervisor?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;No, there is no system approval at this point of time. However, the supervisor will be informed on the selection / rejection of the associate.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Should associates be asked to apply for roles only pertaining to their current service line?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Based on associate’s aspiration, they are open to take any open job role provided they meet the pre-requisite criteria.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Can the supervisor retain the associate in the same account upon successful completion of GenC Digital Honors program or we need to release them from the current project?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If the existing project/account has a new GenC Next / GenC Pro open position available, the selected associate can apply through GenC Digital Honors process and get deployed into the same engagement. If not, they need to be released for opportunities outside the existing project.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have shortlisted an associate for a short-term onsite project, should we stop associates onsite trip or the discourage them from applying for GenC Digital Honors?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is a self-paced learning which can continue from anywhere as long as the associate completes the program as per the timeline. The associate must be available offshore during the selection and deployment phase. &amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Will the associates get promoted from PA to A upon completion of this program?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;No,&amp;#160;they will still be a PA and move into GenC Next/Pro role with enhanced compensation.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div data-sp-canvascontrol=&quot;&quot; data-sp-canvasdataversion=&quot;1.0&quot; data-sp-controldata=&quot;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;position&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;layoutIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;zoneIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;20,&amp;quot;zoneId&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;d6a960bf-57d0-4ed1-95b1-3e0734b0d687&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;sectionIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;sectionFactor&amp;quot;&amp;#58;12,&amp;quot;controlIndex&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1&amp;#125;,&amp;quot;zoneGroupMetadata&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;type&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;isExpanded&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;showDividerLine&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;iconAlignment&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;left&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;displayName&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;Set 2&amp;quot;&amp;#125;,&amp;quot;id&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;quot;bead3871-1b81-466b-b5ea-ea0923c85ed6&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;controlType&amp;quot;&amp;#58;4,&amp;quot;isFromSectionTemplate&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;addedFromPersistedData&amp;quot;&amp;#58;true,&amp;quot;contentVersion&amp;quot;&amp;#58;5&amp;#125;&quot;&gt;&lt;div data-sp-rte=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Will there be a compensation change for the associates who moves to GenC Next/Pro role?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Yes. Currently, the compensation is 6.75 LPA for GenC Next role and 5.40 LPA for GenC Pro role as of Sep 2021 and is subject to change in the future as per HR policies.&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Will there be any change in the performance appraisal process?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The existing performance appraisal process remains the same as the program is like any other project/Job move initiative.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What happens if the associate goes on long leave?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In case the associates need to avail long leave after applying/being selected for the program, the GenC Digital Honors program team should be informed. The associate will be dropped from the current participating cycle and will be allowed to participate in the subsequent cycle.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What happens if an associate moves from PA to A during this program?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;They are still eligible to pursue this program and move to GenC Next / GenC Pro role with enhanced package.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The associate is eligible for PA to A promotion in upcoming cycle, is the program still applicable for the associate to participate?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;GenCs at PA level who are due for promotion can still participate in this program to take up the GenC Next / GenC Pro role. This program does not affect the associate’s existing regular promotion process.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What if the project deliverables are impacted due to this program?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The associates&#39; current work deliverables should not be affected during this learning phase, and they must participate in this program during their non-project hours (this has been communicated as part of program guidelines). If the supervisor still feels that there is an impact on the existing project deliverables / quality due to participation in this program, they need to inform the GenC Digital Honors team who will intervene and set expectations for the associate. If the trend continues, they can be disqualified from the program.&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What if the open position is no longer valid due to unavoidable situations after selecting the associate for the GenC Next / GenC Pro role?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This initiative is driven based on high demand open positions and there would be multiple open positions for the same role. If the open position is no longer valid, the supervisor can work on alternate open SOs with operations / TSC POCs where the GenCs can move to the new GenC Next / GenC Pro roles.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What if the backfill is complete for the potential associate who applied for GenC Digital Honors, but he/she couldn’t clear the interview process? Do they move to PDP?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This initiative is driven based on high demand open positions and it is very unlikely the selected candidates will not end up into the target role. In the event of such an unforeseen scenario, the candidate will be positioned for an alternate open position in this program.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will happen if the backfill is not identified even after ~3 months after associate applied for the program?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This program provides a 3-to-4-month lead time, and it is required by the current project team to identify and have a replacement planned on time to enable the movement of this associate to the GenC Next/Pro role. In the event of any unforeseen delays, as a workaround the current project team can discuss this with associate &amp;amp; PM of the targeted account asking for additional time to be agreed upon by all involved stakeholders.&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GenC joined as PAT is participating in the Honors program, when should we move them/release for higher order role?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;For instance, if a PAT is participating immediately after completing 6 months in Cognizant and completes Honors program by 9&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;#160;month, he/she will be retained in same project till they become PA and post that project team will have additional 6 months to move/release them to a GenC Next role.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div data-sp-canvascontrol=&quot;&quot; data-sp-canvasdataversion=&quot;1.0&quot; data-sp-controldata=&quot;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;controlType&amp;quot;&amp;#58;0,&amp;quot;pageSettingsSlice&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;isDefaultDescription&amp;quot;&amp;#58;true,&amp;quot;isDefaultThumbnail&amp;quot;&amp;#58;true,&amp;quot;isSpellCheckEnabled&amp;quot;&amp;#58;true,&amp;quot;globalRichTextStylingVersion&amp;quot;&amp;#58;1,&amp;quot;rtePageSettings&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;contentVersion&amp;quot;&amp;#58;5&amp;#125;,&amp;quot;isEmailReady&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false,&amp;quot;webPartsPageSettings&amp;quot;&amp;#58;&amp;#123;&amp;quot;isTitleHeadingLevelsEnabled&amp;quot;&amp;#58;false&amp;#125;&amp;#125;&amp;#125;&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</mso:CanvasContent1>
